===Defend Indy Wrestling=== Dennis is the co-founder of "Defend Indy Wrestling", a clothing brand for [[independent wrestling]] fans. Inspired by the "DEFEND Pop Punk" message propagated by American band [[Man Overboard (band)|Man Overboard]], Dennis created the brand in 2011 with fellow British wrestlers [[Pete Dunne (wrestler)|Pete Dunne]] and [[Mark Andrews (wrestler)|Mark Andrews]], producing [[t-shirts]], [[hoodies]] and other accessories.<ref name="theindycorner.wordpress.com">{{cite web|title=10 Questions With … 'Dynamite' Pete Dunne|url=https://theindycorner.wordpress.com/2014/01/07/10-questions-with-dynamite-pete-dunne-dynamitedunne-3/|access-date=2018-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119021102/https://theindycorner.wordpress.com/2014/01/07/10-questions-with-dynamite-pete-dunne-dynamitedunne-3/|archive-date=2015-01-19|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref name="IndyCornerInterview">{{Cite web |title=Eddie Dennis Interview |author= |work=The Indy Corner |date= |access-date=23 October 2018 |url= http://www.theindycorner.com/interviews/eddie-dennis-interview/ |quote=}}</ref><ref name="figh_Hell">{{Cite web |title=Hello Wembley Predictions: Eddie Dennis vs Mark Andrews |author= |work=FightBoothPW |date= |access-date=23 October 2018 |url= http://fightboothpw.com/hello-wembley-predictions-eddie-dennis-vs-mark-andrews/ |quote=}}</ref>
