{{Chinese name|[[Xú|Tsui]]}}
{{Infobox Chinese |title=Tsui Tin-Chau |collapse=no |t=徐天就 |s=徐天就 |p=Xú Tiānjiù |w=Hsü T'ien-Ch'iu |j=ceoi4 tin1 zau6 |y=chèuih tín jauh |bpmf=ㄒㄩˊ ㄊ一ㄢˉ ㄐ一ㄡˋ }} '''Tsui Tin-Chau''' (born in [[Hong Kong]], 1958) ([[Jiaxiang County|jiaxiang]]: [[Guangdong]], [[Zhongshan]]) is a Chinese-born [[Dutch inhabitants|Dutchman]] who is well known in the Chinese community in the [[Netherlands]]. He emigrated to the Netherlands in 1972.
After graduating from [[secondary school]], he completed his studies at the Katholieke pedagogische Academie (Catholic Pedagogical Academy) in Maastricht and his study in [[Oriental Studies|Chinese Languages and Cultures]] at [[Leiden University]].
Tsui teaches Chinese in both [[secondary education|secondary]] and [[tertiary education]]. In addition, he develops educational tools and teaching methods for Chinese language courses and Chinese language (weekend) schools. His course ''Chinees? 'n makkie'' (Chinese? Piece of cake)<ref name="http://www.selexyz.nl/product/9789046900611/t-c-tsui/chinees-n-makkie/?channel_code=210&product_code=27221923&s2m_campaign=top5000_boektitels&gclid=CMG7guP0_K4CFcGEDgodBH2J3g">{{cite book | title=Chinees? 'n makkie! | publisher=Coutinho | author=T.C. Tsui | year=2007 | isbn=9046900614}}</ref> is well known. Until 2010, he was a teacher at Eijkhagen College/Charlemagne College in the Dutch province of [[Limburg (Netherlands)|Limburg]].
Tsui is known in the Chinese community in the Netherlands primarily because of the Chinese broadcast on the Dutch channel [[Nederlandse Programma Stichting|NPS]], ''snelle berichten Nederland-China'' (Quick Messages Netherlands-China). From 1996 to 2005, he presented the Dutch course "''Aa Laa (alle) dingen Yeung Yeung Sóow/阿啦dingen樣樣數''" (“All things Yeung Yeung Sóow/阿啦things樣樣數"). He also presented the course "''Dag in dag uit Nederlands/荷语日日讲''" (Dutch every day 荷语日日讲). Together with Chow Yiu-Fai, Tsui hosted light-hearted summer programs like "''Yauw Moow Kôk Tsôh有冇搅错''".
==Publications== In addition to teaching methods and educational tools, Tsui has published the following works: * T.C. Tsui (1995). ''Chinese Wijsheden en parallelle Nederlandse gezegdes in twee talen'' (Chinese wisdom and parallel Dutch sayings in two languages) * Geense, P. & T.C. Tsui (2001). Chinese: In: G. Extra & J.J. de Ruiter (red). ''Babylon aan de Noordzee. Nieuwe talen in Nederland'' (Babylon by the North Sea. New languages in the Netherlands).
